TITLE: McConnell leads delegation of Republican senators to Kyiv
SUMMARY: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy called the visit a powerful signal of bipartisan support for Ukraine, as well as the American people.

TITLE: Veil of secrecy surrounds the Jan. 6 subpoenas for GOP lawmakers
SUMMARY: Outside of internal ethics probes, there is no modern precedent for a congressional committee subpoenaing members of the House.

TITLE: Senate Dems grab one last chance to push Biden on student debt
SUMMARY: Majority Leader Chuck Schumer, as well as Sens. Elizabeth Warren (D-Mass.) and Raphael Warnock (D-Ga.), are seeking a meeting as soon as possible.

TITLE: Why the Jan. 6 panel bet its legal hand against the House GOP
SUMMARY: There's no guarantee the subpoena of five GOP lawmakers will give the committee more information on former President Donald Trump's attempt to subvert the 2020 election. They're barreling ahead anyway.

TITLE: Dems face facts: They need a November turnaround to save Roe
SUMMARY: The party isn't done voting on abortion rights this year. But its members admit, with striking candor, that they can't pass anything without bigger majorities.

TITLE: Jan. 6 panel subpoenas McCarthy, Jordan, three other GOP lawmakers
SUMMARY: The subpoenas target some of former President Donald Trump’s closest allies in the House, demanding testimony by the last week of May.

TITLE: Senate hustles to pass $40B Ukraine aid package
SUMMARY: Leaders still have to navigate a few hangups, including Sen. Rand Paul demanding an amendment that would designate a federal watchdog to track the money.

TITLE: Senate Democrats’ imaginary majority
SUMMARY: From abortion to Ukraine aid to immigration, the caucus is confronting its “tenuous” control over the chamber.

TITLE: Battle lines harden as Senate prepares to take doomed vote on abortion rights
SUMMARY: The largely symbolic vote to codify abortion protections will fail, with not even a simple Democratic majority supporting the bill.

TITLE: Inflation's biting. Roe's fraying. Dems are still trying to connect with voters.
SUMMARY: Democrats in Congress are rolling out ways to tackle inflation. But they're struggling on another front: Talking about it with the public.

TITLE: House gives green light to staffer unionization
SUMMARY: The Congressional Workers Union has labored behind the scenes for months to jump-start the unionization process among House offices. And they're not alone.

SUMMARY: Two of the Donald Trump-backed TV star's GOP primary rivals in Pennsylvania are blasting his ties to Turkey. But Oz's potential future colleagues don't mind.

SUMMARY: Senate Minority Whip John Thune said Tuesday that negotiators were still trying to “iron out a few matters” and that the total may change.

SUMMARY: The party's No. 2 and No. 3 Senate leaders said they're prepared to take up a proposal that would block President Joe Biden's migration move.

TITLE: Republicans splinter on how to handle a post-Roe world
SUMMARY: The GOP is on different pages about a national abortion ban should the Supreme Court follow through. But pursuing one is certainly on the table.

TITLE: Dem senator spars with Fox News host over Florida law
SUMMARY: Chris Murphy said he perceives a nasty turn in the Republican Party.

TITLE: Supreme Court justices 'misled the Senate,' Gillibrand said
SUMMARY: “If a corporation put these kind of statements in their quarterly filings, they would be seen to be purposefully misleading and deemed fraud,” the New York senator said.

TITLE: No way to negotiate end to Russia-Ukraine war, Graham says
SUMMARY: "There is no off-ramp in this war," the South Carolina Republican said.

SUMMARY: Multiple former aides and other Republicans told POLITICO about the "trauma bonded" work environment of Rep. Victoria Spartz.

SUMMARY: At-risk incumbents are painting themselves as a post-Roe firewall, though neither party has 60 votes to pass either abortion restrictions or protections.

SUMMARY: His Ohio romp is a strong signal that — for all the talk of his waning influence — the GOP is still in his thrall.

SUMMARY: Their preferred vehicle to respond to the Supreme Court breach is all but sure to fail. Whether more abortion debate will follow remains unclear.

SUMMARY: There’s a direct line from the Senate GOP leader's decision to hold a high court vacancy open in 2016 to the potential demise of Supreme Court precedent.

SUMMARY: Members of Congress are already speculating on the ramifications of a world without Roe v. Wade.

TITLE: Schumer vows abortion rights floor fight in wake of Roe draft opinion

TITLE: Klobuchar: Abortion is a ‘decision between me and my doctor. Not Ted Cruz.’
SUMMARY: The Minnesota senator warned that overturning Roe v. Wade would leave the issue of abortion rights up to politicians.

TITLE: Jan. 6 committee asks three pro-Trump GOP lawmakers for testimony
SUMMARY: Reps. Andy Biggs (R-Ariz.), Ronny Jackson (R-Texas) and Mo Brooks (R-Ala.) all voted to object to certifying the former president's loss to Joe Biden.
